  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Interior Sales Designer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>We are an integrated boutique interior design firm that offers suites of solutions from design planning to project management. Established in 2018, we embody the term inizio. We understand the excitement of new home and business owners, and this understanding shows in the quality of our customers’ service. We aim to be with you every step of the way for our goal is to create liveable and functional spaces for our clients.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Lead client engagements by managing enquiries and delivering tailored interior design solutions. Coordinate project execution to ensure timely completion and seamless collaboration with subcontractors and suppliers.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Respond promptly to customer enquiries across diverse property types including HDB, Condominium, Landed, and Office to understand client needs</li><li>Develop accurate quotations aligned with customer requirements and design specifications to support informed decision-making</li><li>Create innovative interior design concepts and space planning solutions that enhance functionality and aesthetics</li><li>Supervise project sites and coordinate activities to maintain quality standards and adherence to timelines</li><li>Schedule and manage workflow effectively to ensure customer move-in dates are met without delays</li><li>Collaborate closely with subcontractors and suppliers to facilitate smooth project execution and resolve issues proactively</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or equivalent qualification or relevant ITE Certificates</li><li>Proficiency in 3D Max, SketchUp, and CAD software to produce detailed design visuals and plans</li><li>Ability to communicate effectively in English and Mandarin to liaise with a diverse customer base</li><li>Demonstrated passion for design and creativity in interior design concepts</li><li>Sales-oriented mindset with the ability to meet monthly KPIs</li><li>Sociable with a positive working attitude conducive to team collaboration</li><li>Minimum of one year of relevant experience in interior design or project coordination</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 1,
